The paper presents Streak, a RDF data management system that is designed to support a wide-range of queries with spatial filters including complex joins, top-k, higher-order relationships over spatially enriched databases. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.DB (Database), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, since the paper focuses on efficient processing of spatial data in RDF/SPARQL, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of a semantics-aware Quad-tree index and adaptive query processing also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.DS and cs.IR. Finally, the experimental evaluations comparing Streak with popular spatial join algorithms and state of the art end-to-end systems like Virtuoso and PostgreSQL suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.SE.
